''Theorem.''
Let all Eigenvalues of $$A \in \R^{n \times n}$$ have $$\Re(\lambda_i)<0$$ and let $$b\colon \R \to \R^n$$ be a bounded function. Then $$\dot{x} = Ax + b(t)$$ has a unique solution which is bounded on $$\R.$$
